4.21 Largest Number Pseudocode
Input 10 Integers
Determines and prints the largest number

a. counter : to count to 10 ( ie keep track of how many numbers have been inputted and to determine when
all  10 numbers have been processed)

b. number: the integer most recently input by the user

c. largest : the largest number found so far.



assign zero to counter as an integer variable
assign zero to largest as an integer variable
initialize variable called number as an integer

while counter <= 10
    prompt the user to enter units sold
    assign unit sold to the variable number
    if ( number > largest )
    largest = number
    increment counter

Output the largest number found

